Language Design and Programming Methodology Symposium
CSIRO DCR Newsletter number 150, December 1979

"Dr. D. Ritchie, of Bell Laboratories, USA, gave a seminar on
"UNIX Portability and the C Language" at the Division on 19
September, 1979. Dr. Ritchie is co-developer of the UNIX
operating system, and he designed and implemented the C
language, in which UNIX is written."
CSIRO Division of Computing Research, Annual Report 1979-80, p 61

"UNIX was implemented in Sydney in March, Melbourne in
April, and Canberra in July.  The version implemented is a
much enhanced level 6 that has been developed at the Uni-
versities of New South Wales and Sydney.  It is referred to as
Australian UNIX Share Access Method (AUSAM)"
