SIROMATH and DMS
"An agreement to make a version of the Bell Laboratories UNIX System III
available in Australia had been concluded with the Division of Computing Research."
CSIRO Division of Mathematics and Statistic, Annual Report 1982

UNIX Distribution
"The Division of Computing Research is finalising
arrangements with the American Telephone and
Telegraph Company to acquire UNIX System III
including the rights to distribute UNIX to third
parties in machine language only.

It is intended that Siromath Pty Ltd, 1 York St,
Sydney, be appointed as the distributor of the
package and to provide the necessary back-up
services required by users."
CSIRONET News, Number 168, December 1982, p 14

SIRONIX Software - UNIX System III
"By the time you read this, SIROMATH Pty Ltd,
under license from CSIRO, will be offering licenses
and maintenance of software derived from UNIX
System III under an agreement signed with the
American group, AT&T.  SIROMATH will market
the software as SIRONIX and it will be available in
binary form."
CSIRONET News, Number 169, February 1983, p 8
